HEADWORD: Uncinus
<hw>Un*ci"nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Uncini</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a hook.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the peculiar minute chitinous hooks found
in large numbers in the tori of tubicolous annelids belonging to the
Uncinata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

